          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>294  fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: H. S. 180; Qurʾānic Text:  complete muṣḥaf; 20 lines per page; Dimensions: 174 x 300mm; Script  style: kūfī; Date of production: 998.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UEN2FUP7" sameAs="UEN2FUP7" type="zotero">Karatay (1962)</ref> describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 23f: "68 H. S. 180. Mushaf. Parşömen. 300mm boy ve 174mm eninde 294 yaprak. Sahifede kûfî ilc 135mm uzunl.[uğunda] 20 satır. Muḥammad b. ʿAlī b. al-Ḥusayn aş-Şaffad eliyle 388 (998) de yazılmıştır. İlk iki sahifesi ve sure başları arap üslûbunda müzehhep serlevhalı. Miklep ve şemşeli vişneçürüğü deri cilt."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "68 H. S. 180. Muṣḥaf. Parchment. 294 leaves of 300 mm height and 174 mm width. The text area, written in Kufic script [contains] 20 lines measuring 135 mm. Written by Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn al-Ṣaffad [al-Ṣafad?], in the year 388 (998). The first two leaves contain sūra beginnings in Arabic style with illuminated serlevha. Cherry brown leather binding with flap (miklep) and mandorla (şemse)."</p>
            </summary>
